cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DS

The paper proposes a label propagation approach to geolocation prediction based on Modified Adsorption, which involves both network analysis and text-based analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with social media data, which suggests cs.SOC (Social Computing) as the second likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper incorporates text-based geolocation priors, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses experiments to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which could be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
